{
  "stem": "25639.9",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How can they treat people like that?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They really reduced us to subhuman level, but we were civilized, fine human beings when we entered the camps.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- those of us who survived, I don't think we'll ever get over the scars of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Never.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think of it all the time and I thank God that I live in this wonderful country, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the United States, where I can enjoy true freedom.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think of what happened to me many times.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I think of all the people in the world who have been-- [CRYING] who have not been so fortunate as I am, to live in freedom, and I hope that someday the world is going to make a strong policy to adopt freedom in their land, because that's the only way, the only way that we can be human beings and we can do the most for our country.",
      "word_count": 70
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "For ourselves and for the country and for the world, just-- through freedom.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But I'd like to go back Sweden-- to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I cannot put into words the wonderful people the Swedish people are.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Swedes really were there when we needed them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They couldn't do enough for us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were kind, gentle, generous in every way, in every way.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Although-- although, I went back and did some research several times to Malmo, I wanted to know what the news was during that year-- during the period when I was incarcerated.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And also, what did the people think about us coming to Sweden?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And once we got there, what-- what was it that they thought about us?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And of course, they had concerns.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
